# Geological Specimen Material Type — SKOS ConceptScheme
# Generated from GeologicalSpecimenMaterialTypes.xlsx
# Source sheets used: Concept Scheme, Concepts, Namespeces, Agents
# Generated: 2026-04-19

# Data issues / transformation notes:
#  1. The namespaces sheet is named "Namespeces" (typo for "Namespaces").
#  2. vocabularyIRI is <http://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-specimen-type>, but concept IRIs live under 2 distinct parent IRI(s):
#       - <https://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-material-type> (does NOT match scheme)
#       - <https://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-specimen-material-type> (does NOT match scheme)
#     Transcribed as-written; reconcile in source if this is unintended.
#  3. Some concepts declare skos:inScheme pointing to an IRI other than the vocabularyIRI <http://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-specimen-type>:
#       - <https://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-material-type>
#     Transcribed as-written; this will cause SKOS scheme membership checks to fail.
#  4. The following skos:broader references point to concepts NOT present in this vocabulary:
#       - 'Rock Core' → <https://vocab.geospecimens.org/def/geological-specimen-material-type/rock>
#     Transcribed as-written.
#  5. vocabularyIRI uses http:// scheme. Concept IRIs in this workbook typically use https://. Consider normalizing to https:// for the scheme IRI.

# Standard prefixes
